##Manufacturers are planning to return to work in March, hoping to save themselves safely

The number of confirmed cases in areas other than Hubei has been slowing down for several days, giving some manufacturers hope that, based on the gradual progress in the prevention and control of the epidemic, a plan for safe return to work and self-help has also begun to be brewing

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Zhang Wei, CAIJING correspondent

Editor | Yuen Man

Wu Jianming, president of 12 parks, 1,500 enterprises and nearly 100,000 employees of Wanyang Group Co. , Ltd. (Wanyang Group) , which is headquartered in Wenzhou, Zhejiang Province, began planning during the Spring Festival period to minimize the damage caused by the epidemic, to realize the safe return to work of its industrial park enterprises as soon as possible.

Wu Jianming told the CAIJING reporter that according to usual practice, manufacturing enterprises this year will generally suspend work on the 15th day of the 12th Lunar Month (January 9) and resume work on the 15th of the 1st Lunar Month (February 8) . They will reserve one month's production materials before the holiday. "looking at the immediate nodes, if the delayed shutdown not only affects the manufacturing industry itself, but also basic material security, some foreign trade companies' customers will move orders to other countries. "

So, he stayed at home through the Wechat conference group, started the resumption of the park program discussions, for more than 10 days a day with the management team to discuss, detailed program.

Among them, "centralized transportation, centralized prevention and Control" , by Wu Jianming and the team that is the most effective workers return to the city program. This can reduce the risks of enterprise employment and pressure on the government to prevent and control, Wu said frankly, the implementation of the program still needs the support of local governments.

In recent years, the industrial cluster represented by the park has developed rapidly. Under this concept, some related industrial chain upstream and downstream industries or different types of enterprises in the same industry form agglomeration in space. The 1500 companies in the Wanyang group all share the common characteristics of manufacturing and are mainly small and medium-sized enterprises.

On January 27, Wanyang group received documents one after another, and the time for the park to resume work was postponed from February 3 to February 9 and February 17. Among them, Guangdong Park can resume work after February 9, Zhejiang Park can resume work on February 17. In the latter case, 60 per cent of the companies in the Wanyang campus will not be operational until mid-march.

How much damage does the delay in starting work do to the enterprise? According to the recent survey on the capacity of enterprises to start construction, led by the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences, 7.1 percent of enterprises can afford to delay the start of construction for more than a month, only 1.7 per cent of companies were able to afford extensions of more than two months.

China has a total of 537 industrial parks in 27 provinces and cities, including those with the name "smart manufacturing, " according to the World Smart Manufacturing Center Development Trend Report 2019. There are more than 9.58 million manufacturing enterprises in China, and more than half of them have registered capital less than 1 million yuan, so their ability to resist risks is weak. It is clear that more manufacturing companies are planning to go back to work.

Chen Huan, Director of the Institute of Microbiology of Zhejiang Province, said the manufacturing sector is expected to function normally in March-april as the epidemic may die off in May as the weather warms up.

The safe and steady expectation of resuming work must be combined with the progress of epidemic prevention and control.

There were 3399 new confirmed cases, 86 new deaths and 4214 new suspected cases in China as of 0.24 on February 7. According to the statistics of the National Health Commission, 558 new cases were confirmed in areas outside Hubei Province at 2400 hours on February 7, the growth rate was decreasing for the 4th consecutive day.

An outbreak expert analyzed that the number of confirmed cases began to decline except in Hubei Province. If this trend can be maintained, it means that the imported epidemic situation in the provinces outside Hubei Province has been under preliminary control. Also be in this major premise, each province also began to make the notice that the enterprise returns to work in an orderly manner. But there will be restrictions in provinces and cities where the outbreak is still severe.

The current epidemic prevention and control work has also entered a new stage, is to control local cases. Therefore, the resumption process must be phased, step-by-step. The process will be based on the development of the epidemic situation, scientific prevention and control, precision measures.

Chen Huan suggested that for Labor-intensive Industries, it is more reasonable to start construction gradually from the region. Cities that are less affected by the epidemic can be chosen to put into production first, or people from the region can be given priority to arrive at their posts.

At present, the number of confirmed cases of the decline in the past few days, so that manufacturing companies see hope.

BACK TO WORK BIG PLAN: Centralized Transportation, closed management

Every manufacturing business owner in the park is plotting how to return to work safely and securely. The results of a survey of one of the parks conducted by Wanyang group showed that 90% of the park's business owners were eager to resume work, and more than 90% of the enterprises had policy support and financial service needs.

The plan of the Rehabilitation Program of the Wanyang group enables the leaders of the working groups in each park to actively contact the local government departments, seek the help of the government, and strive to facilitate the docking of the governments of the places where workers are exported and those of the places where they are imported to carry out the centralized transportation of the resumed workers, the government of the place of export shall organize and complete the centralized export of workers, and the government of the place of import shall do a good job in centralized prevention and control of workers.

If there is no effective connection between the governments of the places where the workers are exported and those of the places where they are imported, the working groups in each park will try to contact and cooperate with the local passenger transport companies to help the enterprises to complete the centralized transportation of workers, centralize prevention and control, and push the enterprises to resume production as soon as possible.

At the same time, they expect to seek government help, commandeer nearby hotels as a centralized quarantine point, to ensure that the quarantine period must meet 14 days.

In addition, to find local third-party labor service cooperation units capable of providing labor transportation in the surrounding areas, and to provide labor support for enterprises that have difficulty in employing people for returning to work. And the park to provide business services to the tenants to give rental concessions.

For the manufacturing industry, it will take some time to adjust, because manufacturing enterprises are very cautious about the production of goods, if the quality is not reasonable, rework will be very troublesome. "In the manufacturing industry, our most intuitive feeling is that if a park is stagnant it won't affect the overall situation, but if there is a general shutdown, it's a very scary thing, " Wu said

Li Huanze, an expert on industrial clusters and a professor at the National Sun Yat-sen University, warned that Labor clustering is one of the most important characteristics of industrial clusters or parks, if someone has a problem, it's easy to have a big system problem.

At the time of the outbreak, the manufacturing enterprises should first provide the basic material production guarantee for the outbreak and the health guarantee for the workers; when the enterprises return to work, they need to fully measure the situation of the improvement of the epidemic, on the basis of safeguarding the physical and mental health of workers, and to carry out organized management. The park needs to do a good job in the systematic management of workers in the park before resuming work, including the management of workers at home before returning to work, health management, the protection and Health Protection of workers in the industrial park after starting work, activity management, etc. , and all kinds of contingency plans and systems.

The practices of some enterprises may serve as a reference for enterprises, Tang Dajie, director of the Research Department of the Saiyi Enterprise Research Institute and a visiting researcher at the Wuhan University, told Caijing, individual enterprises with branches in many parts of the country have planned to move production to other parts of the country to complete more urgent orders from the worst-hit areas to non-worst-hit areas. Of course, there are great constraints, general enterprises do not have the size of the layout of different places, however, the production of self-help is the only possible way to do it.

A person in the industry said that at present, roads are closed and borders are cut off everywhere, and there is a lack of national coordination. From the point of view of the characteristics of manufacturing operations, cutting off a single station means that the entire road system's transportation network is cut off simultaneously, even if the enterprise to resume work, whether the smooth transport also remains to be further observed.

People in the industry further pointed out that the following issues need to be resolved when the manufacturing industry returns to work: First, the manufacturing industry often relies on migrant workers, and how to supplement the industrial workers is a problem that local governments must consider, migrant workers must not feel that this place is closed to outsiders. Once an unfriendly feeling has formed, it will be difficult to absorb it. Second, enterprises must be prepared to fight the epidemic for a long time, especially by organizing production under the epidemic situation, compared with the service sector, the manufacturing sector has the advantage of being able to conduct small-scale production in closed areas. Third, under the epidemic situation, both individuals and enterprises are injured, and the wage arrangements of enterprises should be decided by more market-oriented mechanisms, the premise of enterprise wage increase is to be able to survive. "companies are being asked to pay several times their salaries, and in the short term it is the people who benefit, but in the long term, if the companies can not survive, it is the people who will lose their jobs. "

According to the regulations of the Wanyang Group Park, after the resumption of work, the park will be closed for production. Under the premise of ensuring living materials and materials for prevention and control, the workers of the enterprise will be prevented from entering and leaving the park at will. In case of emergency, the workers of the enterprise must leave the park, must have stamped the enterprise official seal of the proof of the situation, through the Sentry Box Staff Registration can be released.

It is a fundamental understanding that it is impossible to fight an epidemic without normal economic growth and functioning. Tang Dajie believes that the revitalization of the economy, so that the delayed start of the enterprise can be a good start, to give financial support, increase the confidence of business owners. However, I do not agree that it is desirable to force financial institutions to provide low-cost services. Business owners should use their own ability to help themselves, including: Trade Associations (parks) to do some strategies, with the industry to reach consensus, do not engage in price competition, the establishment of a rescue fund, we work through the industry hard times.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
EXPORT-ORIENTED ENTERPRISES: Vacation without rest, high cost to resume work

Export-oriented manufacturing enterprises have a stronger sense of urgency. Ge Wenzhi, who is based in Hangzhou and has left 200 workers to work overtime at the factory this Spring Festival, is pleased with his decision.

With 600 employees and an annual output value of about 500 million yuan, Hangzhou Meidikai Photoelectric Technology Co. , Ltd. mainly produces semiconductor parts and products for export to Japan.

According to Ge Wenzhi, compared with other manufacturing enterprises, employees of his enterprise enjoy only 12 days of vacation every year (7 days of Spring Festival vacation + 5 days of annual vacation) , "companies get orders in advance and then start production, " he said. "This Spring Festival, we planned to finish some orders before the festival, and leave 200 employees to work overtime after the festival. "

On January 20, with no sense of seriousness, GE gave the remaining 400 employees the day off as originally planned, paying 200 overtime workers three times their pay according to state regulations.

At 10:00 on January 23, Wuhan City bus, subway, ferry, long-distance passenger transport was suspended; No special reason, residents do not leave Wuhan, the airport, railway station from the Han Channel was temporarily closed.

The News of the city closure in Wuhan made GE nervous. He returned to Hangzhou from other places in an emergency. He closed the 200-person factory area where he worked overtime. Except for logistics-related personnel, access to and from the factory was stopped, and employees were fed and housed inside the factory.

Ge said the most important export orders have been secured and all 200 remaining workers are in good health.

However, he still faces a difficult decision to start work. If the returning workers are allowed to return without a foolproof quarantine control, then the 200 people in the factory are also at risk of being infected. More worrying is that, part of the staff to the epidemic-prone areas, of which, 10% of the employees in Hubei Province. However, if the field staff do not come back, the future only a third of the staff put into production, also very much impact on business orders.

Ge Zhiwen did not dare to take any chances. After several struggles, he decided to keep employees in high-risk areas such as Hubei temporarily at home until the company notified them to return to work. He also counted workers in other areas who were less affected by the epidemic and were willing to return to Hangzhou, after that, a closure agreement was reached with a local hotel, and employees returned to Hangzhou first to a hotel designated by the company. Each person was isolated for 14 days, and the company arranged for its own personnel to deliver meals. If the employees had no problems with isolation for 14 days, by the special car back to the company to resume work.

According to Ge Zhiwen's plan, starting from February 5, some employees have returned to Hangzhou for self-isolation at the hotel. On February 20, more employees can return to work, but he admitted that before the epidemic is completely over, only about a hundred people have returned to Hangzhou.

Ge Zhiwen calculated a fee, can not come back to the staff enjoy more than 2,000 minimum wage, to be fair, the normal return of the staff, in addition to their monthly wages, plus 2,000 yuan, isolation of the staff each 15 days accommodation 2,700 yuan, about $300,000 is spent on hotel accommodation alone.

Ge Zhiwen knew in his heart that it was no longer a matter of money. The most important thing was to resume production as soon as possible and complete customer orders in a timely manner so as not to affect customer operations, because the export-oriented enterprise customers are easy to other countries and regions of business away.

Bottom line: Preferably in April

From Wu Jianming to Ge Wenzhi, as well as more manufacturers interviewed by the CAIJING reporter, they understand that, despite preparations to return to work, there is still some time before the normal operation of the enterprises.

Tang Dajie told Caijing that unlike the service industry, the manufacturing industry has a cycle problem of logistics and capital flow, from normal start-up to stock-up, production to cash flow back, which is usually a two-month cycle, therefore, even if we start work, it will be a tough two months for those enterprises with financial difficulties. Secondly, the manufacturing industry needs smooth logistics, so the current road closure will further affect the normal operation of the manufacturing industry. Thirdly, the manufacturing industry relies on skilled workers, restrictions on the movement of people in hard-hit areas will further affect the normal operation of enterprises.

Given the current outbreak is difficult to predict, Ge Zhiwen Conservative expectations, that his enterprise as soon as the end of March can be fully back to work (start) . He said that the more the enterprise back to work, the greater the risk of losing business and customers abroad! It will cause irreparable damage!

If the epidemic continues to spread, it will further delay the resumption of work in the manufacturing sector. Wu Jianming has set the limit for April, "If normal work resumes in April, 30 percent of the small and medium-sized enterprises in our park will be hit hard or even close down. " Unlike large enterprises, these enterprises do not have excessive debt ratios because they have less access to financial services, so the credit pressure is not big, moreover enters the park platform the enterprise to be possible to enjoy the certain financial service, their biggest pressure comes from the industrial worker migration which because of the stoppage.

Wu Jianming calculates a detailed account: taking the resumption of work on February 17 as an example, enterprise employees will generally return one after another on February 18 and 19, and then be isolated for 14 days. Another feature of the manufacturing industry is that most of the migrant workers are arriving one after another, for about 10 days. As a result, 60 per cent of his current campus (in Zhejiang Province) will not be operational until at least mid-march.

Several manufacturing business owners interviewed by CAIJING predicted that they would be able to operate normally at least in late March. "To be honest, I don't see a point in time when the manufacturing sector will start to function properly, " Tang said. "Hubei Province will definitely recover more slowly than the rest of the country. Moreover, Hubei is in the heart of China. " Its population and logistics are tied to the nation's business structure, which affects manufacturing across the country and impedes economic recovery as a whole. Second, business owners will scale back their operations if they expect a downturn in the economy.

Rather than wallow in the gloom of the epidemic, he has daily conversations with several business owners about how to start production as soon as possible, how to maximize efficiency and minimize economic impact, according to Wu.

However, these ideas have yet to return to work. Even if they do return to work, they still face problems securing jobs and supplies of raw materials. According to the reporter from Caijing, compared with other industries, manufacturing production has seasonal characteristics. Taking garment production as an example, garment enterprises should prepare autumn and winter clothing at present, and relevant raw materials should also be synchronized to match supply, if the clock runs out, there's no way to schedule production.

In the current special period, manufacturing enterprises are eager to start the need for how much? An epidemic experts to "CAIJING" reporter said that this is to branch industries, the more closely with the people's livelihood of the enterprise, the greater the need to start work early. Of course, according to the current inventory situation and other factors to determine the comprehensive.

For labor-intensive industries, once construction starts, it is essential to establish an epidemic prevention and control management system, draw up epidemic prevention and control emergency plans and working measures, and make clear who is in charge, especially in some environments that are prone to the spread of viruses, such as canteen, toilet, etc. 

The epidemic expert pointed out that the situation in different areas may not be synchronized at present, but may be gradually restored, the first time node is around February 10, because it is scheduled to end the holiday in many areas, some regions and enterprises will try to resume work. The second time point is around February 20, that is, from now on, an additional incubation period (two weeks) will be added to fully resume normal production. It may take about three months, once the new coronavirus infection is fully under control,. However, the situation is likely to change as the epidemic develops and national control measures change.

Chen Huan believes that at present, COVID-19 pneumonia is still highly contagious and the country hopes to control the epidemic as soon as possible, we will encourage enterprises that are essential to epidemic prevention and control, essential to people's livelihood and other enterprises that are important to the national economy and the people's livelihood to resume their work so as to ensure the normal operation of cities. For other types of enterprises, according to the epidemic situation, will gradually clear the conditions for resumption of work. "In recent days, the government has imposed strict controls on companies going back to work, including manufacturing companies, and it is not clear when they will actually start. In fact, this requires an objective assessment of the control of the epidemic at the national level."

"The core issue is that people's expectations of the epidemic are uncertain, and it's not clear when construction will start, when the employees will be able to come back, and whether there will be orders after construction starts, " Tang said. There is a confidence indicator for judging the macro-economy. If confidence is not enough, it is also possible that manufacturing bosses will empty their manufacturing assets and instead hold on to them or transfer them.

Prevention of industrial chain transfer, seeking opportunity in crisis

An owner of a foreign trade manufacturing enterprise told CAIJING that at present, not only does the industrial chain transfer to other countries, but for them, they are more worried that overseas customers will delay the resumption of work and locate irresistible factors and demand compensation.

On the morning of February 2, CCPIT issued the country's first COVID-19 pneumonia force majeure factual certificate to an auto parts manufacturer in Huzhou, Zhejiang Province, of A COVID-19 pneumonia outbreak across the force majeure.

It is understood that the act of factual proof in the field of Commercial Force Majeure means that the CCPIT and its authorized branches and branches shall, upon the application of the applicant, prove the facts relating to the force majeure, after the issuance of the contract, the parties may be exempted from the liability for non-performance, incomplete performance and delay in performance in part or in whole.

Tang Dajie believes that China's manufacturing industry, especially export-oriented manufacturing, has been very difficult since 2018, with a large number of enterprises contracting orders, and some companies that export mainly to the United States are already having difficulty receiving orders. Until 2018 or 2019, export oriented manufacturing will be more difficult, either because it will have to move factories to Southeast Asia or because it will have to upgrade structurally.

In his proposal to the local chamber of Commerce, GE Zhiwen wrote, "for export-oriented manufacturers of industrial goods, the impact and losses can be long-term, or even irreversible losses. Because the current industrial chain is global supply, that is to say, customers'suppliers are located in different countries (regions) . However, this outbreak is mainly concentrated in the mainland of China, and suppliers from other countries (regions) are basically unaffected. It is bound to cause customers to shift their main orders or even all of them to suppliers from countries (regions) outside China. Even if the outbreak disappears and Chinese enterprises can gradually resume normal production, it will be difficult for them to win back the orders.

Made in China has been playing a more and more important role in the global industrial chain with the international competitiveness that has been built up since the Chinese economic reform of the country. "protecting 'made in China' and 'China's economy' should also be an integral part of this epidemic. Government departments at all levels should, on the basis of ensuring health and safety, allow enterprises, especially export-oriented manufacturing enterprises, to resume normal work as soon as possible. "

"enterprises can not rely entirely on state aid, but should help themselves as soon as possible and resume normal production, " Ge Zhiwen told Caijing.

At present, the manufacturing sector accounts for about 30% of the total GDP. Although its contribution to the gross national product has fallen to second place, it still plays an important role. During the key stage of the manufacturing sector's upgrading, the market main analysis believes that, the manufacturing sector will be particularly hard hit by the outbreak, and the main problem will be the loss of confidence among business owners and investors.

Compared with the view that "China's basic consumption is still there, China's manufacturing power status is still there" , Tang's view is not optimistic: things have changed, the basis of economic development is different from 2003, in recent years in a downward channel; in 2019, china's manufacturing sector is in freefall.

Wang Jici, a professor at Peking University's School of urban and environmental studies and a former steering committee member of the International Geographical Union at professor, takes a different view. She believes that the manufacturing industry is experiencing a serious epidemic in its difficult transition, stoppage, shortage of labor, lack of logistics, shortage of cash flow and other difficulties are testing the enterprises and industrial clusters. I believe that particular epidemics can, to some extent, be turned into opportunities for Development, as Jack Ma and Liu Qiangdong did in the year of SARS in 2003. I believe in this epidemic, there is a group of enterprises are confident, is full of energy to do something, when the end of the epidemic this group of enterprises will stand out, showing vitality.

"It's not like there's nothing to do in the manufacturing sector, " Wang said. "For example, there's a shortage of skilled workers in some factories. Setting up an online platform and providing online training is a good choice, rather than waiting to die. "

Because the main problem of manufacturing enterprises to resume work is the return of industrial workers, technicians and managers from various provinces and cities, the characteristics of labor-intensive industries in manufacturing industry also arouse the industry thinking under the epidemic situation.

Li Yun believes that the epidemic may have an impact on the mode of production in the manufacturing sector. Traditional forms of artificial employment are worthy of consideration by manufacturing enterprises. He believes that automation and artificial intelligence will replace more labor in the future, fully automated and intelligent factories, more flexible production organization patterns will emerge, and we need to see not only the impact of the epidemic, but also what it may change, and more to the future production organization pattern changes.

"talent-oriented" is one of the five basic policies of the "Made in China 2025" , whose core is to upgrade manufacturing intelligence, according to an analysis report. It is an inescapable fact that the shortage of high-skilled talents is one of the limiting factors for China's manufacturing industry to become stronger.

Looking ahead to 2020, eou think tank remains firmly optimistic about the development opportunities in the field of smart manufacturing, with autonomous and controllable industrial machines and robots, the digital transformation of traditional manufacturing, the further promotion of the Industrial Internet, and deep-seated artificial intelligence in the manufacturing hinterland, China's intelligent manufacturing will make rapid progress in the new historical era.

Recently, Beijing, Shanghai, Suzhou and other places have come up with measures and opinions to support smes. On the afternoon of February 6, the Guangdong provincial government officially issued several policies and measures to deal with the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic and support enterprises to resume work and production, this paper puts forward 20 policies and measures in five aspects from the key links of further strengthening the work of ensuring the resumption of work and production in enterprises, reducing the cost of employment in enterprises, reducing the burden on enterprises, increasing financial and financial support, and optimizing government services, we will give full support and support to all enterprises affected by the outbreak to resume work and production.

On February 7, the State Council's Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism for COVID-19 infection held a press conference at which Yu Weiping, the vice minister of Finance, said that in accordance with the latest decision of the State Council meeting, the scale of interest subsidy will be increased, instead, 50% of the actual loan interest rate will be granted to enterprises according to the focus of epidemic prevention and control, ensuring that the actual financing cost of enterprises is less than 1.6% .

In the early hours of February 8, the People's Bank of China published on its website an emergency notice from the Audit Office of the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology of the People's Republic of China of the Ministry of Finance on winning the battle to prevent and control the epidemic and strengthening the key guarantee for enterprise financial support in the prevention and control of the epidemic, besides the medical enterprises directly related to the epidemic prevention and control, it also includes the key enterprises that produce the essential necessities of life. And re-emphasize the support through special loans to financial institutions to increase credit support.

In the area of financial credit, the current park industry has a certain advantage, according to Wu Jianming, the park and the bank to maintain close communication, the platform itself will adjust for enterprises, buffer the pressure of funds. Decentralized manufacturing is also under pressure from credit. In addition, the platform enterprise is the factory building mortgage loan, itself has the pledge.

Wang Jici said that innovation cluster is a local cooperative network composed of innovative enterprises, scientific research institutions, universities and other innovative subjects, and is a local environment conducive to enterprises'independent innovation. In China, the problems of the separation, isolation and lack of cooperation of small and medium-sized enterprises are common in the low-end industrial clusters that once produced a large number of export commodities for the world, these industrial clusters are being upgraded to innovation clusters, which have played a major role in the industrial transformation.

Then, under the epidemic situation, temporary suspension of work or temporary closure of enterprises and related organizations may lead to more serious separation and isolation of small and medium enterprises, Wang Jici believes, "Industry Associations, chambers of Commerce, Intellectual Property Services and technology standard-setting bodies all have a role to play in helping firms in clusters weather the storm. Small and medium-sized enterprises should also be able to huddle together for warmth, especially in the labour-intensive sectors most affected by the outbreak."

(interns Zhang Linyi and Wang Yuting contributed research.)
